RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 22000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL REALM was hustled from the gate then bumped lightly with a foe, went three wide around the opening bend, prompted the pace on the outside, took the lead in the two path with three furlongs to run, spun three wide into the stretch under a drive then lost the advantage at the three-sixteenths, fought on well inside of two opponents in the final furlong and narrowly prevailed under strong urging. MICROSCOPE made light contact with a foe just after the start, went two to three wide on the first turn, settled in a good position down the backstretch, chased two then three wide around the far turn, made a bid in the four path into the stretch then took a short lead at the three-sixteenths, battled between foes to the wire and was denied while just able to get the place. JUMPSTER went four wide on the first turn, tracked the pace on the outside, came under urging late on the backstretch, chased three then four wide on the far turn, made a five wide bid into upper stretch, fought outside of two foes while remaining on his inside lead until inside the furlong marker then swapped to the proper lead, continued to tussle with two rivals to the wire and just missed while extremely far clear for the show. GOLDINI was away awkwardly then brushed with a foe, went to the front, showed the way on the inside, lost the lead under strong urging at the three-eighths and tired. AMERICAN LINCOLN stumbled at the start, bumped with a rival after the break then was taken up while pinched back, rounded the first turn in the three path, moved out onto the backstretch, settled on the outside, traveled three wide around the far turn and was no factor. SUPPLY CHAIN was off slow and spotted the front several lengths, saved ground at the rear and faltered.

BOURBON BAY brushed at the start by GENTLEMAN JOE, who broke inwards, showed the way in hand along the inside under some pressure from MUSICAL HEART, got displaced from the front with five-sixteenths to go, took the inside route into upper stretch, grew leg weary and lost action a furlong out and was guided to the outside, placed to a protective hold and pulled up just inside the sixteenth marker and was subsequently vanned off.
